Collaborators Notes


03 Feb 2014 21:27






For the record, this is a collaboration article.

Ed came up with the original idea of a sushi man with a wasabi sculpture, I fed him some ideas, fixed his writing up, and wrote the interview and poem. Thanks to everyone on the forums and chat who helped us out, and

Potentialwonder.

hidemeeee


The sushi man doesn't really know what he wants, though for the moment his goal is to find out what he is searching for. He follows his master's example, because it's all he knows. The master, of course, got his happy ending, but the anxiety of the unknown that he felt before he won his love's heart still remained in the form of the art that he rejected himself.

Something born from love must still learn the meaning of love by itself.










